so, over the past few months, my skin suddenly freaked out and i broke out pretty badly and i didn’t want to overwhelm it with a bunch of products, so i decided to stick to just three — my own little “holy trinity✨” and honestly, these three have been total lifesavers.

first up, i used the vt cosmetics reedle shot 100 to reset my skin. then i followed with the parnell cica manu 92 serum for some soothing vibes. and to finish, i topped it off with the plant base ac clear magic cream to lock everything in.

what’s cool is all three have centella (cica), and my skin seems to really love it. i started seeing improvements pretty fast — my breakouts have calmed down a lot. now i’m just left with some scars, but i’m thinking a peeling solution might help fade those.

that’s my little skincare journey for now! just wanted to share these three products since they really helped me out. if you’re struggling too, maybe try simplifying and sticking to what works for your skin.

.
